Robert E. Chappell Jr., 52 years old, was named senior executive vice president and chief investment officer.
He had been executive vice president of the investments department.
The company's chairman, president and chief executive officer, Robert G. Schwartz, 61, had held the chief investment officer duties.
Separately, Catherine A. Rein, 46, was named an executive vice president with continuing responsibility for the human resources department.
She also assumes responsibility for the medical, company property and services departments from Donald A. Odell, 63, who remains an executive vice president and chief of staff. 

